        "HHRD's operational excellence is evidenced by its ability to scale while maintaining low overhead. The organization reported <cite id=\"14\">$8,817,000 in foreign grants</cite> across 9 recipients in 2023, alongside <cite id=\"15\">$4.8 million in noncash contributions</cite> such as food and medical supplies. This hybrid model of direct service and grantmaking allows them to address both immediate crises and long-term development needs. Their governance is equally strong, featuring a <cite id=\"16\">10-member board</cite> with a comprehensive <cite id=\"17\">conflict of interest policy</cite> and regular <cite id=\"18\">independent audits</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "Helping Hand for Relief and Development (HHRD) is a global humanitarian organization that has been <cite id=\"1\">serving humanity since 1998</cite> by integrating resources for people in need. The organization manages a sophisticated portfolio of programs including <cite id=\"2\">orphan support, healthcare, and emergency relief</cite> across diverse regions such as <cite id=\"3\">Jordan, Haiti, and Pakistan</cite>. HHRD has demonstrated consistent financial growth, reporting <cite id=\"4\">$94,048,415 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year, representing a <cite id=\"5\">3-year revenue CAGR of 8.2%</cite>. The charity is highly regarded for its operational efficiency, maintaining a <cite id=\"6\">91.2% program expense ratio</cite>, which ensures that the vast majority of donor funds directly support its global initiatives. Furthermore, HHRD has achieved a <cite id=\"7\">perfect overall score of 100/100</cite> from Charity Navigator, a distinction it has held for <cite id=\"8\">12 consecutive years</cite>. This rating is underpinned by <cite id=\"9\">100% independent board members</cite> and a <cite id=\"10\">fundraising efficiency of $0.06 per $1 raised</cite>, reflecting a lean and transparent administrative structure.",
